<h2>x-height</h2>
<p>x-height is the distance between the baseline and mid-line; it is the same height as the lowercase letter ‘x’. An increased x-height has one of the most noticeable effects on legibility and readability on screen and in print. However, the reason we want a taller x-height is not so obvious. The short answer is that a taller x-height helps forms appear bigger at text sizes and therefore increases readability.</p>
<div class="row">
<div class="large-3 column">
  <img src="img/x-height2.png" width="351" height="189" alt=""/> 
